  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\n`_burn` method used to be virtual but it was changed in https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/4377. Some contracts deriving from ERC721 may need to perform additional logic before burning the token (e.g. emitting event in ERC-6239). Adding additional method may be confusing since some implementers may use plain `_burn` without extra logic. Is there any reason why `virtual` was removed or can it be restored in future releases?\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n- release: 5.0.1\r\n- can send a PR if needed\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contracts Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n",
