    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @outSH \r\n\r\nSince 5.0, `_burn` is an wrapper around the virtual `_update(address to, uint256 tokenId, address auth)`.\r\nIf you want to perform additional operation on burn operation, this is the one function you should override, as showcased here:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n    function _update(address to, uint256 tokenId, address auth) internal virtual override returns (address) {\r\n        if (to == address(0)) {\r\n            // do you stuff here\r\n        }\r\n        return super._update(to, tokenId, auth);\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n",
